<Page>
    <!-- DATA -->


    <!-- FLOWS -->
    <Flow key="withCancel">
        <Confirm title="Continue / Cancel?" whiteSpace='pre-wrap'>
            Your text here. You can use {{flowArgs.someProperty}} here if they are present.
        </Confirm>
    </Flow>
    <Flow key="customContinue">
        <Confirm title="Continue Only!" alertText="Accept" debug>
            No Choice but to go on!
        </Confirm>
    </Flow>
    <Flow key="aVeryLongConfirm">
        <Confirm title="Very long confirm" whiteSpace='pre-wrap'>
            This is a really long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long text.
        </Confirm>
    </Flow>
    <Flow key="confirmWithCustomDenyText">
        <Confirm
            title="Custom Deny Text"
            denyText="Deny it!!!!"
        >
            Are you from Mars?
        </Confirm>
    </Flow>
    <Flow key="customAcceptWithoutRemovingCancelButton">
        <Confirm
            title="Custom Accept Without Removing Cancel Button"
            acceptText="Please accept!"
            denyText=",,,Deny,,,"
        >
            Howdy partner!
        </Confirm>
    </Flow>

    <!-- PAGE NAV BAR-->
    <PageNavBar label="Features / Flows / confirm">
        <Box
            display='flex'
            justifyContent="flex-end"
            alignItems="center"
            gap="2"
        >
            <Button
                href="/features"
                label="back"
            />
        </Box>
    </PageNavBar>

    <!-- PAGE CONTENT -->
    <PageContent>
        <CodeBlock>
            <Confirm title="Continue / Cancel?" whiteSpace='pre-wrap'>
                Your text here. You can use {{flowArgs.someProperty}} here if they are present.
            </Confirm>

            <Confirm title="Continue Only!" alertText="Accept" debug>
                No Choice but to go on!
            </Confirm>

            <Confirm title="Very long confirm" whiteSpace='pre-wrap'>
                This is a really long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long long text.
            </Confirm>

            <Confirm
                title="Custom Deny Text"
                denyText="Deny it!!!!"
            >
                Are you from Mars?
            </Confirm>
            
            <Confirm
                title="Custom Accept Without Removing Cancel Button"
                acceptText="Please accept!"
                denyText=",,,Deny,,,"
            >
                Howdy partner!
            </Confirm>
        </CodeBlock>

        <Markdown>
            In flows, you can use a Confirm step to show the user information and offer the choice of cancelling the flow.
            This step will show a modal popup including button(s) for either a Yes/No or Yes with custom text (alertText).
        </Markdown>

        <Box
            display="flex"
            flexDirection="column"
            gap="4"
            my="4"
        >
            <Button
                href="flow:withCancel"
                textContent="With Cancel (Normal)"
                data-test-id="buttonWithCancel"
            />
            <Button
                href="flow:customContinue"
                data-test-id="buttonWithCustomContinueAndWithoutCancel"
                textContent="No Cancel, Custom Continue"
            />
            <Button
                href="flow:aVeryLongConfirm"
                textContent="With wrap white spaces"
            />
            <Button
                href="flow:confirmWithCustomDenyText"
                textContent="Custom Deny Text"
            />
            <Button
                href="flow:customAcceptWithoutRemovingCancelButton"
                textContent="Custom Accept Text Without Removing Cancel Button"
            />
        <Box>

    </PageContent>
</Page>
